ll, so I was chosen to go to second grade, just like that. My parents took me out ASAP and enrolled me in a private school.  They scrimped and saved every penny so my sister and I could have a proper education. We were not the only family who were struggling the whole time either. Whoever said this is an idiot and a waste of time and space.  Her argument isn't compelling, it's a fairy tale idea. One where we all live in a perfect world where the government and the community as a whole gives a crap about kids and education. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="836" language="en" documentId="3421" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Jenn OR" date="Aug 29, 2013 7:13PM" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://living.msn.com/family-parenting/the-family-room-blog-post?post=ab228ffc-1e99-4b37-a7b8-0b6a4c3fb240" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="8" thumbsDown="0" origId="3421" notes="" title="Is it wrong to send kids to private school?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="836"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>